A 21-year-old man, Ahmed Lukman, was on Tuesday brought before an Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court for allegedly being in his possession of a double-barrel locally-made gun with the expended cartridge. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1263139" src="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Federal-High-Court-Lagos-1.jpg?resize=640%2C409&#038;ssl=1" alt="VAT, Court remands friends over possession of Indian hemp in Osun" width="640" height="409" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Federal-High-Court-Lagos-1.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Federal-High-Court-Lagos-1.jpg?resize=300%2C192&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Federal-High-Court-Lagos-1.jpg?resize=768%2C491&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Federal-High-Court-Lagos-1.jpg?resize=1024%2C655&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Federal-High-Court-Lagos-1.jpg?resize=58%2C37&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Federal-High-Court-Lagos-1.jpg?resize=260%2C166&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Federal-High-Court-Lagos-1.jpg?resize=200%2C128&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Federal-High-Court-Lagos-1.jpg?resize=560%2C358&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Federal-High-Court-Lagos-1.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The defendant, who claimed to be a welder and resides at 5, Ikosile St., Ijora, Badia area of Lagos, is facing trial for conspiracy and unlawful possession of arm. The Prosecutor, Sgt. Chekube Okeh told the court that the offences were committed on Sept. 14 along Amukoko area of Ijora, Lagos. Okeh said that the police on patrol sighted the defendant and noticed that he looked suspicious. The prosecutor was then accosted, and after searching, a locally made double barrel gun was found in his pocket. “One expended cartridge was also found with him, and when asked where he got it from, he could not give any explanation toward that and so, he was arrested,’’ Okeh said. The offences violated Sections 1 and 411 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. The defendant, however, pleaded not guilty to the charges. The Chief Magistrate, Mrs A.O Akinde, granted the defendant bail of N500, 000 with two sureties in like sum. Akinde adjourned the case until Oct. 21 for mention. Vanguard A Lagos State Magistrate’s Court sitting in Ikeja, presided over by Magistrate A. R. Onilogo, has sentenced a 23-year-old man, Alfred Asuquo, to five years imprisonment without an option of fine for possession of one locally-made, double-barrelled, cut-to-size shot gun without license. June 12, 2015 In "News" The police on Wednesday arraigned three applicants before an Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court for allegedly being in possession of firearms and belonging to an unlawful society. June 19, 2019 In "News" Despite the recent and constant massacre and attack on innocent people by Herdsmen who go about with sophisticated weapons such as ak47 and machetes, both the security operatives and the judiciary are yet to bring to full justice the perpetrators of these heinous crimes. However, an Ikeja Magistrates' Court in… May 11, 2016 In "News"